WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.400
Monica Rogati, who has moved around a little bit, but she's like an important data science

00:00:10.400 --> 00:00:15.880
leader and writer, has like the data science hierarchy of needs, or like the AI, like hierarchy

00:00:15.880 --> 00:00:21.520
of needs. Like at the bottom are things like, like logging and like collecting data, and

00:00:21.520 --> 00:00:26.440
then you like move up and like things like at the middle are like analytics. And things

00:00:26.440 --> 00:00:32.759
like machine learning are like way at the top, like way at the top of this pyramid.

00:00:32.759 --> 00:00:40.480
And in terms of like value that people get, you get a lot of value from analytics, from

00:00:40.480 --> 00:00:46.439
like counting things. You get a lot of value from like your first models you train, you

00:00:46.439 --> 00:00:52.200
know, like simple models, linear models, you know. And it's like, you have to be pretty

00:00:52.200 --> 00:00:56.520
mature. You have to be pretty up to your hierarchy of needs to be able to the point

00:00:56.520 --> 00:01:01.799
where you're like, I need a fancy machine learning model that's like learning nonlinear

00:01:01.799 --> 00:01:09.400
relationships or taking advantage of complicated math. I wouldn't say I'm motivated to work

00:01:09.400 --> 00:01:14.879
on machine learning because it's the thing that like offers the most value, or that it's

00:01:14.879 --> 00:01:19.480
the thing that like solves the most problems. Because I think like the thing that solves

00:01:19.480 --> 00:01:25.519
the most problems is like making data accessible to people in their workplaces, and that they

00:01:25.519 --> 00:01:30.720
have the tools to be able to like do basic analytics or train that first model. Like

00:01:30.720 --> 00:01:37.080
you get the biggest wins at that, at those lower levels. I do think the problems like

00:01:37.080 --> 00:01:47.559
like machine learning tooling is interesting because it is complex, and people enter into

00:01:47.559 --> 00:01:57.400
it with different levels of experience, and being able to build tools to make that process

00:01:57.400 --> 00:02:00.599
more streamlined is like is an interesting challenge.

